A BOOK OF RECORD OF THE SEVERALL PUBLIC

TRANSACTIONS OF THE INHABITANTS OF

SALEM VILLAGE VULGARLY CALLED

THE FARMES

div3.p:
8 Voted that all that have had Grants or may have Grants to build seats in the meatenhouse shall
be confined to build within on yeare or else Loose thire grants and Mr John Leach shall have Liberty
for one yeare yett to bould his pue granted to him or else Loose his grante:

4ly Voated that we mack Choice of Captt Jonathan putnam Liftt Benjamin putnam Joseph putnam or
the majer parte of them to petition to the town of Salem for to Release us from aney further Charge
for ye Repaiering of their metinghous and aney former arears of their minstors:
